Comment: Sometimes there is no reason to lose a game other than perhaps we are playing more games than we are able to manage, or we are moving later at night or early in the morning. I lost this one for who knows what reason. The game was fairly even and I basically gave it away by not paying attention and noticing a really obvious threat. I do a d4 as I can handle a queen game better these days.
This usually means black is going to push his king bishop down and check me. It is annoying really. Not sure if I do the best thing but I do...
a3, and that matter is closed, though I would have preferred to move my knight out or move my pawn to c4. CAn't always get what we want in this game.
He is doing well, with both his knights out. I have only moved out three pawns. Need to start developing some minor pieces.

He is going for a quick castle.

I am a little relaxed with the way the board looks for now. Not good enough to tell who is more developed or not, but everything looks familiar enough for me.
He castles.
Want to let my king bishop out.
Not sure if he had to do that as I usually am not too aggressive with my knights, but it is a common move. I might have thought pawn to b6 and set up a fianchetto but this works too.
set up a castle and develop white bishop a bit.

Getting used to seeing this sort of aggressive type of play, where somebody sets up a few pieces to attack something like a pawn. I am not sure if this is a good or bad play on his part. Seems he has an covered minor piece a bit far down the board from his side.
Easy to ward of the problem, and he moves his knight to...
h6, where its attack capabilities be come pretty limited. I seem to be doing okay.
castle and things don't look too bad for either of us.

In fact here spider777 seems to be getting impatient and trying to force something into happening. I know the feeling and I used to be the same way, especially when the center of the board is all congested. Just trying to chip away at something. Mame something happen. These days I tend to find it is not the end of the world to let a congested board hang around for a while.
